One of the most requested surgeries from our young patients is without any doubts the BBL. 

Buttock enhancement with fat grafting, Brazilian Buttock Augmentation, is typically performed as an outpatient procedure under general anesthesia. First, liposuction is used to harvest the patient own fat from other parts of the body such as the abdomen, thighs, flanks, waist and lower back through very small incisions. Liposuction will leads to improvement in contour of these body areas as it will provide the fat for buttock augmentation. The fat is then processed and injected into the buttock through small incisions of 3 mm in size. The buttocks will look more rounded and naturally lifted.

✨ FACE & NECK LIFT ✨ before & after 

Our beautiful patient before and after 7 weeks from her face and neck lift surgery. 

With Dr. Doumit’s technique, facelift incisions are hidden. They begin in the temporal area above the ear into the hair, follows the contour of the ear and then behind the ear into the hairline. These incisions permit exposure of the deeper facial soft tissues. Descended facial fat will be repositioned to the position of youth. When some individuals have loss of fat in their face, Dr Doumit will add fat, which is taken from another part of the body. Neck improvements are obtained through a small incision under the chin by suturing/tightening the sagging muscle of the neck (corset platysmaplasty). Some excess fat of the neck is occasionally removed. Those techniques allow accurate correction of the laxity noted in the aging neck. They provide a sculptured jawline and a long lasting result.
